# O'Konnolly Budget Tool

A proactive budgeting app for couples — pay down debt while keeping your lifestyle.

## Features

- **Income Tracking**: Combined take-home pay for both partners plus side income
- **Bank Statement Import**: Upload CSV from any bank/credit card to auto-detect spending categories
- **Seasonal Estimation**: Projects a full year of expenses adjusted for seasonal spending patterns
- **Debt Paydown Planner**: Avalanche method optimizer with visual timeline to debt-free
- **What-If Scenarios**: See how cutting expenses or adding income impacts your debt timeline
- **Smart Suggestions**: Personalized recommendations based on your actual spending
- **Post-Debt Savings**: See what your freed-up payments could grow into through investing

## Deploy to Vercel

1. Push this project to GitHub
2. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) and import the repository
3. Click "Deploy" — no environment variables needed (all logic runs client-side)

## Local Development

1. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

2. Run the development server:
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

3. Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- React 18
- Pure CSS (Notion-inspired design system)
- Client-side only — no server, no database, your data stays on your device
